Ext.data.JsonP['Managing_ACLs']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Managing ACLs</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-37548617\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Managing ACLs</h1>\n    <p>Access control lists let you control read and write access to Mobile Backend Services (MBS) objects. Read permission includes the ability to show, query and search MBS objects.  Write permission includes the ability to update and delete MBS objects. An ACL consists of the following:    </p>\n<ul class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>A public read flag granting read permission to all users, <strong class=\" \">or</strong>, a list of users granted read permission    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>A public write flag granting write permission to all users, <strong class=\" \">or</strong>, a list of users granted write permission    </p>\n</li></ul>    <p>An object&apos;s owner always has read and write permission.    </p>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-37548617_safe-id-TWFuYWdpbmdBQ0xzLUNyZWF0aW5nLGVkaXRpbmdhbmRkZWxldGluZ0FDTHM\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Creating, editing and deleting ACLs</span></h2>\n    <p><strong class=\" \">To create an ACL:</strong>    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>On the main Manage Data screen, click <strong class=\" \">ACLs</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click <strong class=\" \">Create</strong> to open the ACL creation form    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Name</strong> field enter a name of the ACL.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Creator</strong> field, click the plus button     <img src=\"images/download/thumbnails/37548617/image2014-3-20_15_2_58.png\" alt=\"images/download/thumbnails/37548617/image2014-3-20_15_2_58.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbnail\" width=\"30\">\n and select the object&apos;s owner from the list of application Users.    </img></p>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n            <p>The object&apos;s owner always has read and write permission.    </p>\n    </div>\n    </li><li class=\" \">    <p>In the <strong class=\" \">Public Read</strong> field, do one of the following:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Select <strong class=\" \">Yes</strong> to allow read access for all users.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Select <strong class=\" \">No</strong> and click     <img src=\"images/download/thumbnails/37548617/image2014-3-20_15_51_23.png\" alt=\"images/download/thumbnails/37548617/image2014-3-20_15_51_23.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbnail\" width=\"30\">\n to select users who should have read access (as shown below).    </img></p>\n    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/37548617/access_list_new.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/37548617/access_list_new.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border\" width=\"600\">\n    </img></li></ol></li><li class=\" \">    <p>Similarly, in the <strong class=\" \">Public Write</strong> field, do one of the following:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Select <strong class=\" \">Yes</strong> to allow write access for all users.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Select <strong class=\" \">No</strong> and click     <img src=\"images/download/thumbnails/37548617/image2014-3-20_15_51_25.png\" alt=\"images/download/thumbnails/37548617/image2014-3-20_15_51_25.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbnail\" width=\"30\">\n to select users who should have write access.    </img></p>\n</li></ol></li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click <strong class=\" \">Save Changes</strong>.    </p>\n</li></ol>    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=37548617\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Managing ACLs"});